HEADWORD: Zinnwaldite
<hw>Zinn"wald*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So called after
<ets>Zinnwald</ets>, in Bohemia, where it occurs.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A kind of mica containing lithium, often
associated with tin ore.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

